str2: But, except, however. Neuter plural of allos; properly, other things, i.e. contrariwise.

str2: From a compound of hupo and a derivative of optanomai; to hit under the eye, i.e. to tease or annoy, subdue.

str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.
Body, flesh; the body of the Church. From sozo; the body, used in a very wide application, literally or figuratively.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: From a presumed compound of doulos and ago; to be a slave-driver, i.e. To enslave.

str2: To proclaim, herald, preach. Of uncertain affinity; to herald, especially divine truth.
Other, another (of more than two), different. A primary word; 'else, ' i.e. Different.

str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.

str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.
Failing to pass the test, unapproved, counterfeit. By implication, worthless.
